Your Honor,

I stand before you today, pleading guilty to the offense of shoplifting a dress worth approximately 2000 pounds. I recognize the gravity of my actions and the impact they have on the victim and society as a whole. While I acknowledge the seriousness of my offense, I want to express my deep remorse for the harm I have caused.

At the time of the incident, I was an 18-year-old high school student, facing financial constraints that made it impossible for me to afford a dress for prom. Impulsively, I succumbed to temptation and attempted to shoplift the dress. However, it is important to note that this was an isolated incident, and I have no prior record of criminal behavior.

I sincerely regret my actions and fully understand the consequences they could have had not only on my own future but also on the trust and safety of the community.

Your Honor, I humbly request that you consider these mitigating factors when determining an appropriate sentence for my offense. Although I cannot undo the past, I am committed to making amends and preventing any recurrence of such behavior.

In closing, I plead guilty to the offense of shoplifting and accept full responsibility for my actions. While I acknowledge the need for appropriate consequences, I respectfully request that the court consider the circumstances surrounding this incident and extend leniency accordingly.

Thank you for your consideration.

