Your Honor,

I stand before you today, pleading guilty to the offense of shoplifting a dress worth approximately 2000 pounds. I recognize the gravity of my actions and the impact they have on the victim and society as a whole. While I acknowledge the seriousness of my offense, I want to express my deep remorse for the harm I have caused.

At the time of the incident, I was an 18-year-old high school student, facing financial constraints that made it impossible for me to afford a dress for prom. Impulsively, I succumbed to temptation and attempted to shoplift the dress. However, it is important to note that this was an isolated incident, and I have no prior record of criminal behavior.

